{
  "texts": [
    "The execution time of a solution was then quantified by the average execution time of the remaining runs.",
    "Outliers were excluded to improve the accuracy of execution time measurements.",
    "Specifically, a significant difference in execution times was observed between runs where no other programs were active on the server and runs where other programs were running concurrently.",
    "This indicates that external factors, such as server load, were affecting the results.",
    "Additionally, the first execution often takes longer due to the absence of cached data."
  ]
}